Activation of Remote Desktop License Server – Detailed Explanation (Exam-Oriented, Based on Microsoft Article)
Remote Desktop Licensing is a critical part of Remote Desktop Services (RDS) provided by Microsoft. According to the Microsoft Learn article, before a license server can issue licenses (CALs) to users or devices, it must be activated. Activation connects the server with Microsoft systems and enables it to distribute licenses properly.
1. What is License Server Activation?
Activation of a Remote Desktop License Server is the process of registering the server with Microsoft so that it can:
Issue Client Access Licenses (CALs) to users/devices
Communicate securely with Microsoft systems
Manage and track license usage
 Without activation, the license server cannot issue permanent licenses and will not function properly.
2. Purpose of Activating License Server
To enable the server to issue licenses (CALs)
To establish a secure connection with Microsoft Clearinghouse
To allow installation and management of licenses
To ensure legal and authorized usage of RDS
 After activation, the license server becomes a registered authority for managing licenses.
3. Prerequisites for Activation (As per Microsoft Article)
Before activating the license server, the following conditions must be fulfilled:
1. Windows Server with Licensing Role Installed
The Remote Desktop Licensing role must already be installed
Licensing tools should also be available
2. Administrative Permissions
The user performing activation must have administrator rights
3. Basic Knowledge of RDS Licensing
Understanding of CALs and licensing types is required
4. Company Information
Details such as name, organization, and region must be provided during activation
 These prerequisites ensure a smooth and successful activation process.
4. Methods to Activate License Server
Microsoft provides three methods to activate the Remote Desktop License Server:
1. Automatic Connection (Recommended Method)
Description
The server connects directly to Microsoft over the internet
How it Works
Uses secure communication (TCP port 443)
Activation is completed automatically through the wizard
Advantages
Fast and simple
Most commonly used method
Use Case
Organizations with internet access on the server can activate quickly without manual steps
This is the recommended method by Microsoft.
2. Web Browser Method
Description
Used when the server does not have internet access
How it Works
Administrator copies a URL from the Licensing Manager
Opens it on another system with internet
Completes activation online and enters the ID back
Advantages
Useful for restricted environments
Use Case
Secure environments where servers are isolated from the internet
 Allows activation even without direct server connectivity.
3. Telephone Method
Description
Activation is done by calling Microsoft support
How it Works
Administrator contacts Microsoft Clearinghouse
Provides required details
Receives activation ID
Advantages
Works without internet
Use Case
Offline environments with no internet access
 Used as an alternative when other methods are not possible.
5. Steps to Activate License Server (Simplified Flow)
Step 1: Open Licensing Manager
Go to Server Manager → Tools → Remote Desktop Licensing Manager
Step 2: Start Activation Wizard
Right-click server → Select “Activate Server”
Step 3: Choose Activation Method
Automatic / Web / Telephone
Step 4: Enter Company Information
Name, organization, country, etc.
Step 5: Complete Wizard
Follow instructions until activation is finished
Step 6: Install Licenses (CALs)
After activation, install purchased licenses
 Activation is completed using the Activate Server Wizard.
6. What Happens After Activation?
License server becomes fully functional
You can install and manage RDS CALs
Server can issue licenses to users/devices
Secure communication with Microsoft is established
 After activation, the server acts as a license registrar.
7. Important Concept – Temporary Licenses
Before activation, the server may issue temporary licenses
These are valid only for a limited time
Permanent operation requires full activation
 Temporary licenses allow short-term usage until activation is complete.
8. Real-Life Use Case
Example Scenario
A company sets up Remote Desktop Services for employees:
Installs RD Licensing role
Activates license server using automatic method
Installs CALs
Employees connect and receive licenses
Without activation, employees would eventually be unable to connect.
